HEADWORD: Cottager
<hw>Cot"ta*ger</hw> <pr>(k?t"t?-j?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who lives in a cottage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who lives on the common,
without paying any rent, or having land of his own.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cottar</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Cotter</ent>⟦br⟧
